      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, the latency and complexity concerns make sense. Given everything you just listed, do you think it's actually feasible to switch to stateless functions without losing the 'intelligent coordination' aspect of the current system? I'm worried that if we pull the plug on the agent runtime, we'll just end up with a bunch of disconnected functions that can't actually perform the complex tasks we need them to. What's your take?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
